test conventions.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;IN-SCOPE FILES\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/docprose/testdata/ or the fixture path selected by TD-036\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/docprose/*_test.go only if needed to lock fixture loading/golden comparison conventions\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-036-prose-quality-pipeline.md only if the selected fixture path needs a minor correction\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;FIXTURE CASES\u0026#xA;- Generic AI-like prose that should be flagged: unsupported robust/comprehensive/seamless claims, vague importance language, filler transitions, repeated openings.\u0026#xA;- Technical DDx prose that should not be over-flagged: headings, lists, ADR/spec terminology, precise implementation references.\u0026#xA;- Vocabulary behavior: accept DDx, bead, Helix, Fizeau-like project terms when configured; reject known filler when unsupported.\u0026#xA;- Mode differences: technical, planning, and public prose.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;OUT-OF-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- CLI command implementation.\u0026#xA;- Default skill text.\u0026#xA;- Review integration.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Fixture Markdown files cover positive and negative examples for generic AI-like prose, technical DDx prose, project vocabulary, and at least two prose modes.\u0026#xA;2. Expected findings are stored in a machine-readable golden format with file, line, rule id, severity, rationale, and suggested edit fields.\u0026#xA;3. A focused test such as `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/docprose/... -run TestFixtures` passes, or if the package does not exist yet, the bead creates the minimal package/test harness needed for fixture validation.\u0026#xA;4. The fixtures include at least one negative case proving technical lists/headings/domain terms are not automatically findings.\u0026#xA;5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:docs, area:cli, kind:test, prose-quality\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \